# KidStory core rules

English-learning SPA for children: storybooks, course units, vocabulary games, progress/rewards.

## Stack

React 19, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind v4, react-router-dom, Dexie (IndexedDB). See `AGENTS.md` for routes and folder map.

## Do

- Keep changes focused; match surrounding style (`satisfies` on data exports, two-space indent)
- Put session logic in `src/hooks/`; pages in `src/pages/`; pure logic in `src/lib/`
- Use `cn()` from `src/lib/utils.ts` for Tailwind class merging
- Use `useUserProgress()` for unlock state, rewards, hints, and shop
- Run `npm run lint` before finishing; run `npx tsx src/lib/<file>.test.ts` when changing tested lib code

## Don't

- Reintroduce `@luckyluu/wonder-ui` — use Radix wrappers in `src/components/ui/` (see `radix-ui.mdc`)
- Add Jest/Vitest — tests are standalone `npx tsx` scripts with `assert()`
- Rewrite unrelated components or expand scope beyond the task

## Quick paths

- Routes: `src/App.tsx`
- Course registry: `src/data/course/index.ts`
- Game topics: `src/data/games.ts`
- Books: `src/data/books.ts`
- Practice router: `src/pages/CourseUnitPracticePage.tsx`
